(1) The Minister may, by statutory instrument, make regulations for any matter which may be prescribed in terms of this Act and generally for the better carrying out of the objects and purposes of this Act.
The Minister may, by statutory instrument, make regulations for any matter which may be prescribed in terms of this Act and generally for the better carrying out of the objects and purposes of this Act.
(2) Without derogation from the generality of the provisions of subsection (1), the Minister may make regulations providing for— (a) the admission of the public to the National Archives and the inspection by the public of the public archives ; (b) the transfer of any public records to the National Archives ; (c) responsibilities of public officers for the custody of public records ; (d) the conditions under which documents in the National Archives may be reproduced or published or extracts made therefrom; (e) the fees to be paid for the use of the facilities of the National Archives and for any service provided by the Director ; and (f) the preservation and protection of public archives .
